title: BJP picks Union minister Rajeev Chandrasekhar as state president for new Kerala push
Judge cash row: Probe against Yashwant Varma may not conclude early
Punjab cops looted from protest sites, say farmers

Hospitals asking for money biggest chunk of Ayushman Bharat grievances
SC to hear plea against demolition of house over 'anti-India slogan'
Shiv Sena men attack Mumbai hotel after comedian show with Shinde jibe

description: The DGCA has mandated Indian airlines to inform passengers about their rights when booking air tickets. This measure aims to educate passengers, particularly first-time flyers, about entitlements concerning delays, cancellations, denied boarding, and baggage issues. Airlines must provide an online passenger charter link via SMS, WhatsApp, ticket, and their website. IndiGo has begun implementing this directive.
title: With tickets, send flyers link to their rights, DGCA tells airlines
Anger and fear? More tourists are turning away from Trump's America

description: Stephen Hawking's 1966 PhD thesis, Properties of Expanding Universes, laid the groundwork for his renowned contributions to cosmology and black holes. It explored singularities, the role of general relativity, and how the universe expands. His work provided vital theoretical support for the Big Bang model.
title: Instant Scholar: Stephen Hawking’s PhD thesis on 'Properties of Expanding Universes'
SC allows audit regulator's proceedings against CAs

description: Volodymyr Zelenskyy has called for increased international pressure on Russian President Vladimir Putin to end the ongoing invasion. Amid US-Ukrainian ceasefire discussions in Saudi Arabia, Zelenskyy emphasised that without global pressure, Russia would continue to prolong the conflict and ignore diplomacy. Negotiations are focused on a potential ceasefire in the Black Sea, but Putin has only agreed to halt strikes on energy infrastructure.
title: Zelenskyy says must 'push Putin' to stop strikes, halt invasion
All roads lead to Ladakh: Centre goes full throttle on connectivity after end of 370
India-EU FTA game changer for German industries, investment into India: German envoy
Soon builders performance, details of projects will be easier to track on RERA websites across country

description: Tesla investor Ross Gerber has called for Elon Musk's removal as CEO, criticizing the Tesla board for negligence and the brand erosion following Musk's Twitter acquisition. Gerber, with substantial Tesla shares, believes Musk's divided attention harms Tesla and argues for a dedicated CEO to refocus on the core business.
title: Tesla investor who said Elon Musk 'Not Suited' to run Twitter, now asks Tesla Board to 'fire' him
Crowd-control measures avert tragedy at New Delhi Railway Station

description: Afghanistan's Noor Ahmad made a stellar debut for CSK, taking a four-wicket haul to lead his team to a win over MI in their IPL 2025 opener. His performance restricted MI to 155/9, with Ahmad outshining with 4 for 18. Rachin Ravindra’s unbeaten 65 ensured CSK’s chase was successful, sealing victory in 19.1 overs.
title: IPL 2025: Noor Ahmad's dream debut helps CSK outclass MI

description: Canadian Prime Minister Mark Carney has called a snap election for 28 April, seeking a strong mandate. Carney plans to support farmers, address US trade tensions, and expand dental care. This follows Justin Trudeau's resignation, who faced criticism over living costs and political instability after leading since 2015.
title: Canada's new PM Mark Carney calls snap election for April 28

description: Carlos Carrasco has signed a one-year, $1.5 million deal with the New York Yankees after an impressive spring training. His 1.69 ERA over five games caught the team's attention. With injury concerns in the Yankees' pitching staff, Carrasco's experience is seen as pivotal. The Yankees hope his strong spring performance continues into the regular season.
title: Carrasco earns major league contract with Yankees after spring training

description: Charles Leclerc, Lewis Hamilton, and Pierre Gasly were disqualified from the Chinese Grand Prix due to technical infringements. Leclerc's and Gasly's cars were underweight, and Hamilton's car had excessive skid block wear. This led to a significant reordering of race results, impacting Ferrari's and Alpine's standings in the 2025 F1 season.
title: Lewis Hamilton and Charles Leclerc disqualified from Chinese GP

description: Morgan Stanley analyst Adam Jonas predicts a rebound for Tesla stock, suggesting a potential 93% increase within the next year despite current challenges. The analyst maintains an overweight rating for Tesla, highlighting advancements in robotics and AI as key drivers for future growth.
title: Morgan Stanley's longtime Tesla analyst lowers price target, but retains buy rating

description: MS Dhoni, at 43, performed a quick stumping to dismiss Mumbai Indians’ captain Suryakumar Yadav in the 11th over. His exceptional reflexes and skillful wicketkeeping were the highlight of the match, contributing to Chennai Super Kings' pressure on Mumbai Indians. This moment showcased Dhoni's enduring prowess and impacted Mumbai Indians' innings significantly.
title: Watch: Vintage Dhoni rolls back the years to dismiss SKY

description: Aishwarya Rai, labeled as "one of the most beautiful women in the world," has faced criticism for her acting. Her husband Abhishek Bachchan defended her, highlighting her diverse roles. Aishwarya’s illustrious career includes winning the Padma Shri and Order of Arts and Letters. Rumors of marriage troubles circulate as they appeared separately at a wedding.
title: When Abhishek Bachchan gave fitting reply to those who call Aishwarya 'plastic'

description: Ishan Kishan smashed his maiden IPL century for Sunrisers Hyderabad in just 45 balls against Rajasthan Royals, leading the team to a formidable 286/6. His explosive performance included a brutal onslaught on Jofra Archer's bowling, setting up an 85-run partnership with Travis Head and ensuring a comfortable victory for SRH.
title: IPL: Kishan becomes SRH's newest hero in record IPL onslaught

description: Rohit Sharma became the second-most capped player in IPL history in Mumbai Indians' season opener against Chennai Super Kings. He also equalled the record for the most ducks in the tournament's history with his 18th duck. Despite this, it was a significant achievement in his IPL journey, which started in 2008 and includes five IPL titles with Mumbai Indians.
title: Rohit Sharma equals unwanted IPL record with duck against CSK

description: Istanbul Mayor Ekrem Imamoglu, a major opposition figure, was arrested on corruption charges, sparking significant protests across Turkey. Supporters claim the charges are politically motivated to hinder his presidential ambitions, while the government denies interference. The events have drawn international criticism and led to economic instability.
title: Turkey crisis deepens: Erdogan's political rival jailed; protests intensify
Big encounter underway in J&K's Kathua; 3-5 terrorists cornered near Pak border

description: UPS guidelines: The Pension Fund Regulatory and Development Authority (PFRDA) has introduced guidelines for the Unified Pension Scheme (UPS), effective April 1, 2025. This scheme offers central government employees currently enrolled in the National Pension Scheme (NPS) a comprehensive alternative.
title: UPS rules: Central government employees take note!

description: Samajwadi Party chief Akhilesh Yadav defended MP Ramjilal Suman's remark calling Rana Sanga a "traitor," arguing that referencing historical events should not be problematic. Suman had made the comment while criticizing BJP's labeling of Muslims as Babur's descendants. This has sparked controversy with BJP accusing SP of insulting the Rajput and Hindu communities.
title: Akhilesh Yadav defends Ramjilal Suman's 'Rana Sanga traitor' remark

description: Ross Gerber, CEO of Gerber Kawasaki, criticized Elon Musk for neglecting Tesla and causing negative publicity through divisive actions. He suggested Musk should focus solely on Tesla or step down. The company is facing declining sales and worldwide protests, causing significant brand damage.
title: Angry investor: 'Musk has just destroyed Tesla's reputation with his ... '
China's military embraces 'DeepSeek', deploys AI tool in hospitals

description: Arvind Kejriwal criticizes both BJP and Congress for neglecting Bhagat Singh and BR Ambedkar’s legacies, alleging collusion between the two parties. At a rally, he highlights BJP's removal of iconic pictures and Congress's silence, labeling BJP’s actions worse than British colonial rule.
title: Kejriwal returns swinging, calls BJP ‘worse than British’, hits out at Congress

description: Captain Shubman Gill faces high expectations in IPL 2025 after a disappointing 2024 season for Gujarat Titans. Glenn Phillips emphasises that team performance isn't solely about the captain, noting Gill's experience with high-pressure situations for India. Phillips and his brother, Dale, are renowned for their exceptional fielding skills, attributed to genetics and dedicated practice.
title: Pressure on Gill? Phillips says 'you don't get more pressure than playing for India'

description: Rohit Sharma has achieved the distinction of becoming the second-most capped player in IPL history with his 258th match appearance. He surpassed Dinesh Karthik and now only trails MS Dhoni. Rohit's IPL journey has been marked by his significant contributions both as a batsman and leader, helping Mumbai Indians secure five IPL titles.
title: Rohit hits another milestone before taking field in IPL 2025

description: Nvidia's new Blackwell AI chips surpass their previous Hopper models, rapidly depreciating the value of older GPUs. This quick technological advancement may negatively impact major cloud companies like Amazon, Microsoft, Google, and Meta by accelerating asset depreciation and reducing their operating income.
title: How Nvidia CEO’s 'Blackwell joke' may not be so for it’s biggest customers

description: India has imposed anti-dumping duties on five products from China, including vacuum flasks and aluminium foil, to protect local industries. These duties, based on recommendations from the DGTR, will be in effect for up to five years and also apply to imports from other countries like Japan, Korea, and Malaysia.
title: India imposes anti-dumping duties on five Chinese products

description: Rajasthan Royals pacer Jofra Archer set an unwanted IPL record by conceding 76 runs in his four-over spell against Sunrisers Hyderabad. This performance is now the most expensive in IPL history. SRH's Ishan Kishan scored a rapid century, leading his team to a huge total of 286 for 6, the second-highest in IPL history.
title: Jofra Archer records most expensive spell in IPL history

description: Pope Francis made his first public appearance in over five weeks from the Gemelli Hospital balcony after battling severe pneumonia. He thanked the crowd and is advised to avoid large gatherings for two months. While his ability to attend upcoming events remains uncertain, he is determined to continue his papacy.
title: Pope Francis makes first public appearance in 5 weeks

description: Sunrisers Hyderabad set an imposing total of 286/6 against Rajasthan Royals in IPL 2025, nearly breaking their own record. The innings was highlighted by Ishan Kishan's unbeaten 106 off 47 balls. Supported by key contributions from Travis Head and others, SRH's relentless batting continues to dominate, underscoring their formidable prowess in the league.
title: Record! SRH score second highest IPL total; Kishan slams ton

description: Shekhar Kapur criticized an OTT platform for streaming an edited version of his film 'Bandit Queen' without his consent, raising concerns about creative control. Filmmakers like Hansal Mehta and Tigmanshu Dhulia supported Kapur, emphasizing the ethical issues of post-release edits. The debate highlights the need for clearer guidelines and protections for directors in the digital streaming era.
title: Shekhar Kapur vs OTT censorship on 'Bandit Queen': Battle for creative control

description: Amazon and Tesla are among the top beneficiaries of the H-1B visa program in 2025, securing thousands of approvals. These companies rely on skilled foreign workers for roles in engineering and research. Amazon leads with 9,265 approvals, followed by Cognizant and Google. Indian IT firms like Infosys and TCS also feature prominently among top H-1B visa recipients.
title: Amazon, Tesla & other US companies that bagged maximum H-1B visas in 2024
Sambhal violence: Jama Masjid Sadar chief Zafar Ali arrested

description: The United States has lifted its bounty on Sirajuddin Haqqani, the Taliban's interior minister, as well as bounties on Abdul Aziz Haqqani and Yahya Haqqani. This development coincided with the Taliban's release of American prisoner George Glezmann.
title: US removes $10m bounty on Taliban's Sirajuddin Haqqani: Report

description: CCTV footage reveals controversial preacher Bajinder Singh assaulting individuals, including a woman with a child, sparking outrage. Singh is also under investigation for sexual harassment following a complaint by a 22-year-old. Despite his significant social media following, Singh's history of legal issues raises serious concerns.
title: Watch: Self-styled prophet Bajinder Singh assaults woman in office

description: The Bihar School Examination Board (BSEB) has reportedly announced the Class 10 and 12 result dates. Class 10 results will be declared on April 5, 2025, and Class 12 results on March 27, 2025. Students can check results at secondary.biharboardonline.com. The exams were conducted from February 1-15 (Class 12) and February 17-25 (Class 10).
title: BSEB Bihar Board Result 2025 dates announced? Check details here

description: A Hong Kong Airlines flight had to make an emergency landing in Fuzhou after a power bank caused a fire in the overhead compartment. The fire was quickly extinguished, and no injuries were reported. Authorities are investigating the incident, highlighting the risks associated with power banks on flights.
title: Hong Kong flight makes emergency landing after 'power bank fire'

description: Muskan Rastogi, accused of murdering her husband with her lover, seeks a government-appointed lawyer after her family withdrew support. The couple, struggling in jail, exhibit signs of drug withdrawal. Deceived by messages after the crime, the murder was revealed on March 18. Muskan's family demands the death penalty.
title: Meerut murder case: Muskan seeks govt lawyer as family cuts ties

description: New Zealand clinched a series victory by defeating Pakistan by 115 runs in the fourth T20I. The hosts set a challenging target of 220/6 and bowled out Pakistan for 105, with Jacob Duffy and Zak Foulkes leading the attack. Finn Allen's rapid fifty and Michael Bracewell's unbeaten 46 boosted New Zealand's innings.
title: New Zealand hand Pakistan their biggest T20I defeat to clinch the series

description: Activist Prashant Kishor has questioned Bihar CM Nitish Kumar's mental fitness, demanding his resignation and claiming he is unaware of state affairs. Kishor's comments have intensified criticism ahead of the upcoming elections, despite reassurances from Kumar's allies about his health.
title: 'Nitish mentally unfit, impossible PM unaware': Prashant Kishor's big charge

description: RSS general secretary Dattatreya Hosabale has identified individuals with an 'invader mindset' as a threat to India and criticized the glorification of figures like Aurangzeb. He emphasized that religion-based reservations are unconstitutional and opposed by Dr BR Ambedkar's principles.
title: People with invader mindset are a threat to India: RSS' Dattatreya Hosabale

description: A road accident on the Srinagar-Sonamarg road in Ganderbal district of Jammu and Kashmir resulted in the deaths of four people and injuries to 17 others. The collision between a bus and a taxi, which bore a Madhya Pradesh registration number, occurred at Gund. The injured are undergoing treatment, and officials are determining further details.
title: 4 dead, 17 injured in bus-taxi collision on Srinagar-Sonamarg road

description: Elon Musk reaffirmed his ambition for Mars exploration, mentioning potential human missions by 2029 or 2031 using SpaceX's Starship. A recent setback occurred when the Starship exploded during a test flight, highlighting the technical challenges ahead. Despite this, SpaceX celebrated its 23rd anniversary, continuing its pursuit of making life multi-planetary.
title: Elon Musk shares his photo with 'Mars caption': But then ...

description: In response to attacks on Himachal Pradesh buses in Punjab, Deputy Chief Minister Mukesh Agnihotri announced that the buses will not be parked overnight in Punjab until the AAP government ensures their safety. The vandalism involved smashing windshields and scribbling pro-Khalistan slogans. Measures are being taken to safeguard buses and passengers, including potentially suspending some routes.
title: Himachal halts overnight bus parking in Punjab over pro-Khalistani slogans, attacks
Judge cash row: Burnt Rs 500 notes 'found' near Justice Varma's house

description: Ahead of the IPL 2025 clash between MI and CSK, Rohit Sharma shared a heartwarming moment with a young fangirl who tried to touch his feet. Humbly stopping her, Rohit signed her customised jerseys with respect for the national flag and posed for a photo. MI look to recover from a poor 2024 season, with Suryakumar Yadav leading against CSK.
title: Watch: Rohit Sharma fulfils fangirl's dream by signing customised jersey

description: Undertrials Muskan Rastogi and Sahil Shukla remain in separate barracks at Meerut District Jail, experiencing severe withdrawal symptoms from drug addiction. Muskan is accused of murdering her husband, Saurabh Rajput. Investigations reveal the couple’s long-term drug use and Sahil’s involvement with black magic.
title: 'Demanding injections': How Saurabh Rajput murder accused are spending nights in jail

description: Twitter's former blue bird logo was sold for $34,375 in an RR Auction event after Elon Musk rebranded Twitter to X. The 560-pound sign, known as "Larry," was part of a broader auction of Twitter memorabilia and tech collectibles, including a $375,000 Apple-1 computer and an $87,514 first-generation iPhone.
title: Iconic Twitter logo, blue bird 'Larry' auctioned for nearly $35,000

description: US tourism faces a decline, with international visitors projected to drop by 5.1% in 2025. Factors include policies by President Trump, a strong dollar, and rising global tensions. The tourism sector risks losing $64 billion as a consequence, impacting major upcoming events.
title: ‘Effects of antipathy’: Is US seeing a drop in tourist arrivals?

description: BJP MP Ravi Shankar Prasad criticizes Rahul Gandhi for questioning India's merit system and doubts Gandhi's own qualifications for his role as the leader of the opposition. Gandhi's remarks highlighted the biases in India’s education and bureaucratic systems against Dalits, OBCs, and tribals.
title: 'His tutor should be changed': BJP takes a dig at Rahul over 'merit' remark

description: Rajya Sabha MP Kapil Sibal urged the INDIA alliance to present a united front with a formal structure and clear spokespersons. Highlighting internal conflicts, he emphasized the necessity for a cohesive policy approach to effectively counter the BJP. Sibal also discussed potential challenges and political implications related to upcoming issues like the Waqf (Amendment) Bill and delimitation.
title: INDIA must appear to be a ‘bloc and not un-bloc' itself in public domain: Kapil Sibal

description: Irfan Pathan has been excluded from this season’s IPL commentary panel over allegations of bias against certain players. The former cricketer has previously had conflicts that influenced his commentary and social media posts. Pathan has now launched his YouTube channel.
title: IPL 2025: Irfan Pathan's commentary role cut over player bias?

description: A 17-year-old boy and girl were discovered hanging from a tree in Deer Park, Delhi on March 23, suggesting a suspected suicide pact. The incident was reported by a security guard. Police launched an investigation, and the bodies were sent for examination. The area, known for its restaurants and shops, is being further scrutinized.
title: 17-year-old boy, girl found hanging in Delhi's Deer Park

description: Ex-Australia cricketer David Warner expressed frustration on Saturday about boarding an Air India flight without pilots, leading to hours of delay. The airline attributed the issue to weather-related disruptions at Bengaluru airport, which delayed the flight crew. Air India apologised for the inconvenience, explaining that crew delays affected the flight's departure.
title: David Warner hits out at Air India: 'No pilots, waiting for hours'

description: A fire broke out backstage at the France Pavilion in EPCOT at Walt Disney World, causing no injuries. The blaze began in a walk-in cooler and was quickly extinguished. Videos on social media showed smoke rising as authorities continued their investigation during the busy Spring Break season.

Delhi high court judge Yashwant Varma has vehemently denied allegations regarding the discovery of burnt currency at his residence after a fire incident. He calls the claims baseless and asserts that no cash was ever kept in the storeroom by him or his family. A three-member inquiry committee has been set up to investigate the accusations.
title: Cash row inquiry report: 'No cash was ever placed in storeroom', claims Justice Varma

description: Saritha Ramaraju, 48, has been charged with murder after allegedly killing her 11-year-old son during a custody visit in California. The incident occurred after a trip to Disneyland, with the child found deceased in their hotel room. Additional charges include using a knife. If convicted, she faces 26 years to life in prison.
title: Indian-origin woman charged with murdering son after Disneyland trip

description: The Supreme Court has initiated an inquiry into the fire at Justice Yashwant Varma's residence, where burnt currency notes were allegedly found. Justice Varma denies any wrongdoing, calling the allegations a conspiracy. A three-member panel will investigate the case and review forensic findings.
title: ‘No proof of forced entry’: Key details from Delhi HC CJ’s report on judge cash row

description: A friendly cricket match titled 'Neta XI Vs Abhineta XI' was held in Mumbai to raise awareness about tuberculosis. The game was attended by Bollywood stars including Salman Khan and political figures such as Maharashtra Deputy CM Eknath Shinde. The match was organized by former Union Sports Minister Anurag Thakur.
title: Salman Khan, Maharastra Deputy CM Shinde attend sports event in Mumbai

description: In the IPL 2025 opener, Virat Kohli led Royal Challengers Bengaluru to a commanding win over Kolkata Knight Riders, scoring an unbeaten 59. Chasing down 175 in just 16.2 overs, RCB started strong with a 95-run opening partnership between Kohli and Phil Salt. Despite mid-innings stumbles, RCB secured victory with 22 balls to spare.
title: WATCH: Kohli fan breaches security to touch RCB star's feet

description: Jondalagatti village in Haveri district, known as the 'Village of Bachelors,' faces issues with infrastructure, healthcare, and communication that discourage prospective brides. Consequently, the village is seeing a decline in new school enrollments due to the lack of children.
title: Why this village in Karnataka a red flag for brides-to-be

description: Delhi government plans to ban soaps and detergents in car washes to reduce the phosphates and surfactants entering the Yamuna. A campaign will raise public awareness, and car-wash centers near sewage treatment plants might be set up to use treated wastewater. This initiative aims to tackle the toxic froth and pollution choking the river.
title: Cleaning up Yamuna act: Delhi may ban use of soaps, detergents in car washes

description: Fugitive businessman Mehul Choksi, accused of defrauding Punjab National Bank, is living in Belgium after securing residency. Indian authorities are seeking his extradition. Choksi left India in 2018 and his whereabouts have frequently changed, previously residing in Antigua and Dominica before moving to Belgium.
title: Fugitive businessman Mehul Choksi living in Belgium: Report

description: George Foreman, the two-time world heavyweight boxing champion and Olympic gold medalist, passed away on March 21, 2025, at the age of 76. Known for his incredible punching power and remarkable comeback, Foreman's legacy extends beyond boxing as an entrepreneur and devout preacher, inspiring many with his perseverance and reinvention.
title: George Foreman death: NFL stars Brett Favre, Russell Wilson, and more mourn

description: Imarat Shariah, a major Muslim organisation in Bihar, has refused Chief Minister Nitish Kumar's Iftaar invitation, protesting his support for the Waqf Bill. They allege the bill will harm Muslims’ economic and educational status. Accusing Kumar of betraying his secular promises, the group deems his actions as tokenism. JD(U) has yet to respond.
title: Muslim body declines Bihar CM Nitish Kumar’s Iftaar invitation over Waqf bill
Can Heathrow nightmare hit Indian airports?
Do foreigners have free speech rights in the United States?
Fadnavis hints at Malegaon link to Nagpur riots, says int'l elements' role being probed

description: Israel launched airstrikes on multiple locations in Lebanon, killing at least six people in retaliation for a rocket attack. Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu ordered strikes on Hezbollah targets, raising concerns about the fragile ceasefire. Hezbollah denied responsibility for the attack, and Lebanese leadership stressed they do not seek a return to war.
title: Israel launches airstrikes on Lebanon in largest attack since ceasefire

description: Cognizant Technology Solutions has sold its 13.68-acre property in Chennai for Rs 612 crore. This sale is part of Cognizant's efforts to consolidate operations within three other buildings in Chennai. The new India headquarters will be at the MEPZ campus. The buyer, Bagamane Group, is expected to redevelop the Thoraipakkam property.
title: Cognizant sells the building from where it rang Nasdaq bell

description: A tragic shooting in Virginia claimed the lives of Pradeep Patel and his daughter Urmi, causing shockwaves in both the Gujarati community in the US and their native village in Mehsana. Pradeep, 56, died on the spot while Urmi succumbed to injuries two days later; the suspected shooter has been arrested.
title: Gujarati father, daughter shot dead in US store

description: Despite more women entering the legal profession, the CLPR report reveals systemic gender discrimination in judicial appointments in India. Women judges serve shorter tenures and are appointed at older ages, hindering their rise to senior ranks, including the Supreme Court collegium.
title: Women Supreme Court judges serve 1 year less than men, finds report

description: A Rajkot woman's second marriage was declared null after her husband proved her first marriage was still valid at the time of her second marriage. He argued that their caste did not recognize customary divorce, which she used to end her first marriage. The Gujarat High Court overturned the family court's dismissal of his suit, deeming it legally unsound.
title: Second husband uses wife’s divorce decree to annul marriage in Gujarat
